  "prompt": "Did islam exist before prophet mohmmad?",
  "response": "No, Islam as a formal religion did not exist before Prophet Muhammad. However, Muslims believe that the core principles of Islam - submission to one God and following divine guidance - have existed since the beginning of human history.\n\nAccording to Islamic belief:\n\n1. Prophet Muhammad (born around 570 CE) is considered the final messenger of God and the seal of prophets.\n\n2. Muslims believe that earlier prophets like Abraham, Moses, and Jesus were also Muslims in the sense that they submitted to God's will and preached monotheism.\n\n3. The Quran, which was revealed to Muhammad, is seen as the final divine revelation, completing and confirming previous scriptures.\n\n4. Prior to Muhammad, people might have followed earlier revelations like the Torah and the Gospel, but Islam as a distinct, codified religion began with Muhammad's prophethood around 610 CE.\n\n5. The term \"Islam\" literally means \"submission to God\" and is believed to have been the fundamental message of all prophets throughout history.\n\nSo while the core spiritual principles of Islam are seen as timeless, Islam as an organized religion with its specific practices, laws, and teachings was established through Prophet Muhammad in the early 7th century CE.",
